The right side of the barrel is marked “IMPORTER - PERAZZI – USA / ROME – NEW YORK”. The left side of the top barrel is marked “CAM. 70”, a single star, “18.4”. the left side of the bottom barrel is marked “KG1 550” and “18.4”. The underside of the bottom barrel is marked “ACCIAIO SPECIAL”. The underside of the barrel lug is marked “57783 / MAP / L” There are additional Italian proofs, they are lightly struck, and the date code “AH” in a square. The forend wood is marked “R1217TZ”. The forend hardware is marked “57783”. The receiver has the Italian firing proofs and the right rail on the receiver is marked “PU 57783 MAP”. At the safety it is marked “BLOCCATO”. The rubber recoil pad is marked “KICK-EEZ”.Barrel Length: 28 5/16”Choke: The top barrel is fixed Full /Xtra Full (roughly .96mm), the bottom barrel accepts removable chokes. Perazzi chokes are numbered in 1/10th of a mm based off the actual bore. The chokes included are numbered 2, 3, 4, 5, 2x number 6, 7, 11. This gives the shooter a wide range of choke choices from Improved Cylinder (#2) to Extra Full (#11). There are total of 8 chokes, one in the gun and seven in the case. Two of the chokes are number 6.Sights / Optics: This shotgun is mounted with a bead at the muzzle and a mid bead on the high ventilated rib.Stock Configuration & Condition: The stocks are High Grade and beautifully figured SEO wood. The comb is adjustable and the right side of the pistol grip has a palm swell. The forend and pistol grip are finely hand checkered. The gun has been used in Competition Pigeon shoots, invite only… so there is some light handling wear and honest use to the stock from a responsible sportsman. They are so seldom and light you likely won’t even notice unless you are looking for marks. The checkering is still sharp, no wedding band dings to the forend or divorce marks to the front strap of the pistol grip. Almost as if the gun was handled with gloves. The LOP measures 14.75” from the front of the trigger to the back of the KICK-EEZ recoil pad. The drop at heel above the recoil pad is 2”. The drop at the rear of the adjustable comb is currently 1 3/8”. The drop at comb is 1 ½”. The top of the pad has been shaved for less snag when mounting from low gun. The stocks rate in about Excellent overall condition.Type of Finish: Blue and CoinFinish Originality: OriginalBore Condition: The bore is bright. There is no erosion.Overall Condition: This shotgun retains about 97% of its metal finish. The balance of the finish shows typical finish loss to the barrels from the installation and disassembly of the forend. There is typical wear from light use and operation. The SEO engraving is sharp and detailed. It is so beautiful with delicate little lines, no mars running through it anywhere. The backside of the trigger guard where the middle finger rubs has some finish loss. There is a scratch on the right side of the bottom barrel just in front of the forend. The top of the rib has some thinning to the finish. The screw heads are sharp. The markings are clear and crisp. Overall, this shotgun rates in about Excellent condition.
